quran[431]{c,v,t}:
  67,1,"Blessed is He in Whose Hand is the dominion, and He is Most Capable of all things"
  67,2,"Who created death and life to test you as to which of you is best in deeds, and He is the All-Mighty, the Most Forgiving"
  67,3,Who created seven heavens one above another; you will not see any imperfection in the creation of the Most Compassionate. Look again; can you see any flaw
  67,4,Then look again and again; your sight will turn back to you humbled and weary
  67,5,"We have adorned the lowest heaven with lamps and have made them as missiles to stone the devils, and We have prepared for them the punishment of the Blazing Fire"
  67,6,For those who disbelieve in their Lord there will be the punishment of Hell. What a terrible destination
  67,7,"When they are thrown in it, they will hear its roaring as it boils up"
  67,8,"almost bursting in fury. Every time a group is thrown in it, its keepers will ask them, “Did there not come to you a warner?”"
  67,9,"They will say, “Yes, a warner did come to us, but we denied and said, ‘Allah has not sent down anything; you are greatly misguided.’”"
  67,10,"And they will say, “If only we had listened or understood, we would not be among the dwellers of the Blazing Fire.”"
  67,11,Thus they will confess their sins. So away with the dwellers of the Blazing Fire
  67,12,"Indeed, those who fear their Lord unseen will have forgiveness and a great reward"
  67,13,"Whether you speak secretly or openly, He is All-Knowing of that which is in the hearts"
  67,14,"Does He not know His Own creation, when He is the Most Subtle, the All-Aware"
  67,15,"It is He Who made the earth smooth for you, so travel through its regions and eat from His provisions. And to Him is the resurrection"
  67,16,"Do you feel secure that He Who is in the heaven will not cause the earth to sink with you, then suddenly convulse"
  67,17,"Do you feel secure that He Who is in the heaven will not send against you a storm of stones? Only then would you know how [serious] My warning was"
  67,18,"Those who came before them rejected [the messengers]; then how severe was My response"
  67,19,"Do they not see the birds above them, spreading out and folding in their wings? None holds them up except the Most Compassionate. He is indeed All-Seeing of everything"
  67,20,Which is your army that can come to your aid against the Most Compassionate? The disbelievers are in utter delusion
  67,21,Who is there to give you provision if He withholds His provision? Yet they persist in arrogance and aversion
  67,22,"Who is better guided: the one who walks stumbling and falling on his face or the one who walks upright on a straight path"
  67,23,"Say, “It is He Who brought you into being and gave you hearing, sight, and hearts; little do you give thanks.”"
  67,24,"Say, “It is He Who has dispersed you throughout the earth, and to Him you will be gathered.”"
  67,25,"They say: “When will this promise come to pass, if you are truthful?”"
  67,26,"Say, “That knowledge is with Allah alone, and I am only a clear warner.”"
  67,27,"Then when they see it approaching closer, the faces of the disbelievers will be distressed, and it will be said, “This is what you were asking for.”"
  67,28,"Say, “What do you think, if Allah causes me and those who are with me to die or shows us mercy, who will save the disbelievers from a painful punishment?”"
  67,29,"Say, “He is the Most Compassionate; we believe in Him and put our trust in Him. You will come to know who is clearly misguided.”"
  67,30,"Say, “What do you think, if your water were to sink deep into the earth, who can bring you flowing water?”"
  68,1,Nūn. By the pen and what they write
  68,2,"By the grace of your Lord [O Prophet], you are not madman"
  68,3,You will surely have a never-ending reward
  68,4,"Indeed, you are of a great moral character"
  68,5,Soon you will see and they will see
  68,6,which of you is afflicted with madness
  68,7,"Indeed, your Lord alone knows best who has strayed from His way and those who are rightly guided"
  68,8,So do not obey the deniers
  68,9,They wish that you would compromise so they would too compromise
  68,10,And do not obey every disgraceful swearer
  68,11,"backbiter, gossip-monger"
  68,12,"withholder of good, transgressor, sinful"
  68,13,"coarse, and furthermore, an illegitimate child"
  68,14,Simply because he has wealth and children
  68,15,"When Our verses are recited to him, he says, “Ancient fables!”"
  68,16,We will soon brand him on the snout
  68,17,"Indeed, We have tested them [the Makkans] as We tested the people of the garden, when they swore to harvest its fruits in the early morning"
  68,18,"and made no exception [by saying: if Allah wills]"
  68,19,Then it was struck by an affliction from your Lord while they were asleep
  68,20,and it turned to ashes as black as night
  68,21,Then in the early morning they called out to one another
  68,22,“Go early to your garden if you really wish to harvest.”
  68,23,"So they set out, whispering to one another"
  68,24,“Not a single poor person should enter your garden today.”
  68,25,"And they left early, fully determined to stick to their plan"
  68,26,"But when they saw the garden, they said, “We must have lost our way"
  68,27,"Rather, we have been deprived.”"
  68,28,"The best among them said, “Did I not say to you to glorify Allah?”"
  68,29,"They said, “Glory be to our Lord! We were truly wrongdoers.”"
  68,30,"Then they turned to one another, throwing blame"
  68,31,"They said, “Woe to us! We were surely transgressors"
  68,32,Our Lord may give us something better than this. We certainly turn to our Lord in hope.”
  68,33,"Such is the punishment [in this world]; but the punishment of the Hereafter is far worse, if only they knew"
  68,34,"Indeed, the righteous will have gardens of bliss with their Lord"
  68,35,Should We then treat Muslims like the wicked
  68,36,What is the matter with you that you make such a judgment
  68,37,Or do you have a scripture in which you read
  68,38,that you will be given whatever you choose
  68,39,"Or do you have a solemn promise binding upon Us until the Day of Resurrection, that you will have whatever you decide for yourselves"
  68,40,Ask them which of them can guarantee that
  68,41,"Or do they have associate-gods? Then let them bring forth their associate-gods, if they are truthful"
  68,42,"On the Day when the Shin [of Allah] will be uncovered, and they are invited to prostrate, but they will not be able to do so"
  68,43,"Their eyes will be downcast, overwhelmed with humiliation, for they were invited to prostrate when they were capable [but they refused]"
  68,44,"So leave to Me those who reject this message [O Prophet]. We will gradually lead them to their ruin in ways that they do not perceive"
  68,45,"I will give them respite, but My plan is firm"
  68,46,"Or are you asking them for a reward, so they find it too burdensome"
  68,47,"Or do they have knowledge of the unseen, so they write it down"
  68,48,"So be patient with the decree of your Lord, and do not be like [Jonah], the man of the Whale, when he cried out in anguish"
  68,49,"Had it not been for the grace that he received from his Lord, he would have surely been thrown at the barren shore, blameworthy"
  68,50,"But his Lord chose him, and made him one of the righteous"
  68,51,"The disbelievers would almost strike you down with their malicious gazes when they hear the Reminder, and they say, “He is certainly mad.”"
  68,52,But it is nothing other than a reminder to the whole world
  69,1,The Inevitable Hour
  69,2,What is the Inevitable Hour
  69,3,How do you know what the Inevitable Hour is
  69,4,Thamūd and ‘Ād denied the striking calamity of the Hour
  69,5,"As for Thamūd, they were destroyed by a dreadful blast"
  69,6,"And as for ‘Ād, they were destroyed by a furious windstorm"
  69,7,"which He unleashed against them for seven successive nights and eight days, so you would see the people lying dead as if they were hollow trunks of palm trees"
  69,8,Do you see any trace of them now
  69,9,"Also Pharaoh and those who came before him, and the overturned cities [of Lot] committed grave sin"
  69,10,"each disobeying the messenger of their Lord, so He seized them with a severe punishment"
  69,11,"Indeed, when the floodwater overflowed, We carried you [O humans] in the sailing Ark"
  69,12,"so that We might make it a reminder for you, and that attentive ears may take heed"
  69,13,Then when the Trumpet is blown with a single blast
  69,14,and the earth and mountains are lifted up and crushed with a single blow
  69,15,on that Day the Inevitable Event will occur
  69,16,And the sky will split asunder and will be frail on that day
  69,17,"with the angels on all its sides, and on that Day, eight [mighty angels] will bear the Throne of your Lord above them"
  69,18,"On that day, you will be brought forth [before Allah], and none of your secrets will remain hidden"
  69,19,"As for the one who is given his Record in his right hand, he will say, “Here is my Record, read it"
  69,20,I was sure that I would meet my reckoning.”
  69,21,So he will be in a pleasant life
  69,22,in a lofty garden
  69,23,with clustered fruit within his reach
  69,24,"[They will be told,] “Eat and drink joyfully for what you did in the days gone by.”"
  69,25,"As for the one who is given his Record in his left hand, he will say, “Would that I had not been given my Record"
  69,26,nor had I known anything of my reckoning
  69,27,"Would that it [death] had been the end of me"
  69,28,My wealth has been of no avail to me
  69,29,My authority has vanished.”
  69,30,"[It will be said,] “Seize him and shackle him"
  69,31,then make him burn in the Blazing Fire
  69,32,then tie him up with chain of seventy cubits long
  69,33,"For he did not believe in Allah, the Most Great"
  69,34,nor did he encourage feeding the needy
  69,35,So Today he will have no close friend here
  69,36,nor any food except the discharge of wounds
  69,37,none will eat it except the sinners.”
  69,38,I swear by what you can see
  69,39,and what you cannot see
  69,40,"Indeed, this is the word of a noble Messenger"
  69,41,and it is not the word of a poet; little do you believe
  69,42,Nor is it the word of a soothsayer; little do you take heed
  69,43,It is a revelation from the Lord of the worlds
  69,44,If he had falsely attributed something to Us
  69,45,We would have surely seized him by the right hand
  69,46,then severed his aorta
  69,47,and none of you could have rescued him
  69,48,"This [Qur’an] is indeed a reminder for those who are righteous"
  69,49,And We surely know that some of you will be deniers
  69,50,and it will certainly be a source of regret for the disbelievers
  69,51,And this is indeed the absolute truth
  69,52,"So glorify the name of your Lord, the Most Great"
  70,1,A challenger asked for a punishment bound to come
  70,2,"upon the disbelievers, which none can avert"
  70,3,"from Allah, Lord of the pathways of ascent"
  70,4,by which the angels and the Spirit will ascend to Him on a Day the length of which is fifty thousand years
  70,5,"So be patient [O Prophet] with beautiful patience"
  70,6,"Indeed, they see this [punishment] far off"
  70,7,but We see it to be close at hand
  70,8,On the Day when the sky will be like molten brass
  70,9,and the mountains will be like dyed wool
  70,10,and no close friend will ask about another
  70,11,even though they will see one another. The wicked will wish he could ransom himself from the punishment of that Day by offering his children
  70,12,and his wife and his brother
  70,13,and his kindred who stood by him
  70,14,"and everyone on earth, just to save himself"
  70,15,By no means! It is a raging Flame
  70,16,that will strip off the scalps
  70,17,It will call everyone who turned their backs and disobeyed
  70,18,and amassed and hoarded wealth
  70,19,"Indeed, man was created impatient"
  70,20,"when evil befalls him, he bewails"
  70,21,"but when good fortune comes his way, he becomes tight-fisted –"
  70,22,except those who pray
  70,23,who are steadfast in their prayers
  70,24,and who give a due share of their wealth
  70,25,to the beggar and the dispossessed
  70,26,and who firmly believe in the Day of Judgment
  70,27,and those who fear the punishment of their Lord –
  70,28,for none can feel secure from their Lord’s punishment –
  70,29,and those who guard their private parts
  70,30,"except from their wives or bondwomen whom they own, for then they are not to be blamed"
  70,31,"But whoever seeks beyond that, it is they who are the transgressors"
  70,32,and those who fulfill their trusts and pledges
  70,33,and who are upright in their testimonies
  70,34,and who take due care of their prayers
  70,35,they will be honored in gardens
  70,36,"What is the matter with the disbelievers that they are rushing towards you [O Prophet]"
  70,37,"from the right and from the left, in crowds"
  70,38,Does everyone of them aspire to enter a garden of bliss
  70,39,By no means! We have created them from what they know
  70,40,I swear by the Lord of the sunrises and sunsets that We are surely Capable
  70,41,"to replace them with others better than them, and none can escape Our decree"
  70,42,So leave them to engage in their falsehood and amuse themselves until they meet their Day which they are promised
  70,43,the Day when they will rush out of their graves as if they are racing towards a goal
  70,44,with their eyes downcast and overwhelmed with disgrace. That is the Day that they were promised
  71,1,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people, “Warn your people before there comes to them a painful punishment.”"
  71,2,"He said: “O my people, indeed I am a clear warner to you"
  71,3,"that you worship Allah and fear Him, and obey me"
  71,4,"He will forgive you some of your sins and grant you respite until an appointed term. Indeed, when Allah’s appointed term comes, it cannot be delayed, if you only knew!”"
  71,5,"He said, “My Lord, I have surely called my people night and day"
  71,6,but my call only drove them further away
  71,7,"Every time I call them so that You may forgive them, they thrust their fingers into their ears and cover their faces with their garments, and persist in obstinacy and grow extremely arrogant"
  71,8,Then I called them openly
  71,9,then I addressed them in public and in private
  71,10,"I said, ‘Seek forgiveness from your Lord. Indeed, He is Most Forgiving"
  71,11,He will shower you with abundant rain from the sky
  71,12,"and He will give you wealth and children, and bestow upon you gardens and rivers"
  71,13,What is the matter with you that you do not fear the Majesty of Allah
  71,14,when He has created you in stages
  71,15,"Do you not see how Allah has created seven heavens, one above another"
  71,16,and has placed the moon therein as a light and the sun as a burning lamp
  71,17,Allah has produced you from the earth like a plant
  71,18,"then He will return you into it, and then will bring you out again"
  71,19,Allah has made the earth wide spread for you
  71,20,so that you may tread its spacious paths.’”
  71,21,"Noah said, “My Lord, they have disobeyed me and followed those whose wealth and children did not increase them except in loss"
  71,22,They have contrived a mighty plot
  71,23,"They said, ‘Do not abandon your gods; and do not abandon Wadd, Suwā‘, Yaghūth, Ya‘ūq, and Nasr.’"
  71,24,"They have led many astray. So [O Lord], do not increase the wrongdoers except in error.”"
  71,25,"Because of their sins they were drowned and then were cast into the Fire, and they did not find any helpers against Allah"
  71,26,"Noah said, “My Lord, do not leave on earth a single disbeliever"
  71,27,"For if You leave them, they will surely lead Your slaves astray and beget none but wicked disbelievers"
  71,28,"My Lord, forgive me and my parents, and whoever enters my house as a believer, and all the believing men and women, and do not increase the wrongdoers except in ruin.”"
  72,1,"Say, “It has been revealed to me that a group of jinn listened [to the Qur’an,] and they said, ‘Indeed, we have heard a wondrous recitation"
  72,2,"that guides to the right way, so we have believed in it, and we will never associate anyone with our Lord"
  72,3,And that He – our exalted and glorified Lord – has neither taken a wife nor a child
  72,4,"and that the fool among us [Satan] used to say outrageous things about Allah"
  72,5,although we thought that humans and jinn would never tell lies about Allah
  72,6,"And there were some men who used to seek refuge with some jinn, but they only increased them in burden"
  72,7,"They thought, just like you [jinn] thought that Allah would never send any messenger"
  72,8,We have sought to reach the heaven but found it filled with stern guards and flaming fire
  72,9,"We used to take up positions there for eavesdropping, but now anyone who eavesdrops will find a flaming fire waiting for him"
  72,10,"We do not know whether evil is intended for those on earth, or their Lord intends good for them"
  72,11,"Among us are some who are righteous and some who are otherwise, for we follow divergent ways"
  72,12,"We have realized that we can never escape Allah on earth, nor can we ever escape Him by fleeing"
  72,13,"When we heard the guidance [of the Qur’an], we believed in it. Whoever believes in his Lord will have no fear of curtailment [from his reward] or injustice"
  72,14,Among us are some who are Muslims and some who are deviant. Those who accepted Islam have sought the true guidance
  72,15,"but those who are deviant, they will be fuel for Hell.’”"
  72,16,"“If they had remained steadfast on the right way, We would have given them abundant rain"
  72,17,"as a test for them. But whoever turns away from the remembrance of his Lord, He will make him suffer an arduous punishment"
  72,18,"The mosques are for Allah alone, so do not supplicate anyone along with Allah"
  72,19,"Yet when the slave of Allah stood up supplicating Him, they swarmed around him.”"
  72,20,"Say [O Prophet], “I only supplicate my Lord and I do not associate anyone with Him.”"
  72,21,"Say, “I have no power to harm or benefit you.”"
  72,22,"Say, “None can ever protect me from Allah [if I should disobey Him], nor can I ever find a refuge other than Him"
  72,23,"I only convey what I receive from Allah and His messages.” And whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger will certainly be in the Fire of Hell, abiding therein forever"
  72,24,"Until when they see what they were promised, they will realize who is weaker in helpers and fewer in number"
  72,25,"Say, “I do not know if what you are promised is near or my Lord has appointed a distant time for it"
  72,26,"[He is] Knower of the unseen, He does not reveal His unseen to anyone"
  72,27,"except the messenger whom He chooses, then He appoints angel-guards before him and behind him"
  72,28,"to ensure that the messengers fully conveyed the messages of their Lord. He encompasses in His knowledge all about them, and keeps count of all things.”"
  73,1,O you the enwrapped one
  73,2,Stand up in prayer at night except a little
  73,3,"half of it, or a little less"
  73,4,"or a little more, and recite the Qur’an at a measured pace"
  73,5,We will send down upon you a heavy revelation
  73,6,"Indeed, prayer at night is more effective and more conducive to proper recitation"
  73,7,"In daytime, you have plenty of time for your worldly matters"
  73,8,"And remember the Name of your Lord, and devote yourself completely to Him"
  73,9,"[He is] Lord of the east and the west; none has the right to be worshiped except Him, so take Him as Disposer of your affairs"
  73,10,"Bear patiently what they say, and avoid them in a gracious manner"
  73,11,"Leave to Me the deniers who are having a life of luxury, and bear with them for a little while"
  73,12,"Indeed, We have heavy shackles and a Blazing Fire"
  73,13,"and food that chokes, and a painful punishment"
  73,14,"on the Day when the earth and the mountains will convulse, and the mountains will be like dunes of loose sand"
  73,15,"Indeed, We have sent to you a Messenger to be a witness over you, just as We sent to Pharaoh a messenger"
  73,16,"But Pharaoh disobeyed the messenger, so We seized him with a severe punishment"
  73,17,"If you disbelieve, then how will you protect yourselves against a Day that will turn children’s hair gray"
  73,18,It will cause the sky to break asunder. His promise will certainly be fulfilled
  73,19,"Indeed, this is a reminder; so whoever wills may take a way to his Lord"
  73,20,"Indeed, your Lord knows that you [O Prophet] stand up in prayer for nearly two-thirds of the night, or half of it, or one-third of it, as do others among your companions. Allah determines the night and the day; He knows that you [Muslims] cannot keep an accurate count of it, so He pardoned you. Recite then as much of the Qur’an as is easy for you [in the night prayers]. He knows that there are some among you who will be ill, and others traveling in the land, seeking the grace of Allah, and others fighting in Allah’s way. So recite as much of it as is easy for you; establish prayer and give zakah; and lend to Allah a goodly loan. Whatever good you send forth for yourselves, you will find it with Allah, much better in condition and much greater in reward. And seek forgiveness of Allah, for indeed Allah is All-Forgiving, Most-Merciful"
  74,1,"O you covered [in your cloak]"
  74,2,arise and warn
  74,3,and proclaim the greatness of your Lord
  74,4,and purify your garments
  74,5,and shun idol worshiping
  74,6,and do not do a favor for a greater return
  74,7,and be patient for the sake of your Lord
  74,8,When the Trumpet is sounded
  74,9,that Day will be a difficult day
  74,10,not easy for the disbelievers
  74,11,Leave me alone to deal with the one whom I created
  74,12,and gave him abundant wealth
  74,13,and sons by his side
  74,14,and gave him a life of comfort and power
  74,15,yet he aspires that I should give him more
  74,16,By no means! For he has been stubborn against Our verses
  74,17,I will subject him to an unbearable punishment
  74,18,"For he reflected and plotted [against the Qur’an]"
  74,19,"May he perish, how he plotted"
  74,20,"Again, may he perish, how he plotted"
  74,21,Then he looked around
  74,22,then he frowned and scowled
  74,23,then turned away with arrogance
  74,24,"then said, “This is nothing but magic from the past"
  74,25,This is nothing but the words of a man.”
  74,26,Soon I will make him burn in the Scorching Fire
  74,27,How do you know what Scorching Fire is
  74,28,It leaves nothing and spares no one
  74,29,scorching the skin
  74,30,"It is overseen by nineteen [angels]"
  74,31,"We have only appointed angels as keepers of the Fire, and We have only made their number as a test for the disbelievers, so that those who were given the Scripture may have certainty and the believers may increase in faith; and neither those who were given the Scripture nor the believers may have any doubts; and so that those [hypocrites] in whose hearts is sickness and the disbelievers may say, “What does Allah mean by this number?” Thus Allah causes to stray whom He wills and guides whom He wills, and none knows the soldiers of your Lord but He. This is but a reminder to mankind"
  74,32,No indeed! By the moon
  74,33,and by the night when it departs
  74,34,and by the dawn when it brightens
  74,35,Hellfire is indeed one of the greatest matters
  74,36,a warning to mankind
  74,37,to whoever among you chooses to advance or regress
  74,38,Every soul is held in pledge for its deeds
  74,39,except the People of the Right
  74,40,"who will be in gardens, asking one another"
  74,41,about the wicked
  74,42,“What brought you to Hell?”
  74,43,"They will say, “We were not among those who prayed"
  74,44,nor did we feed the poor
  74,45,and we indulged in falsehood along with those who indulged in it
  74,46,and we denied the Day of Judgment
  74,47,"until the certainty [of death] came to us.”"
  74,48,So the intercession of intercessors will not benefit them
  74,49,Then what is the matter with them that they turn away from the Reminder
  74,50,as if they were terrified wild asses
  74,51,fleeing from a lion
  74,52,"In fact, each one of them desires that open [divine] letters be sent to each of them"
  74,53,By no means! They rather do not fear the Hereafter
  74,54,"No indeed! This [Qur’an] is a reminder"
  74,55,So whoever wills may take heed
  74,56,But they will not take heed unless Allah so wills. He is most worthy to be feared and most worthy to forgive
  75,1,I swear by the Day of Resurrection
  75,2,and I swear by the self-reproaching soul
  75,3,Does man think that We cannot reassemble his bones
  75,4,"In fact, We are able to restore even his very fingertips"
  75,5,But man desires to persists in his evil ways
  75,6,"and asks [mockingly], “When is the Day of Resurrection?”"
  75,7,But when eyes are dazzled
  75,8,and the moon is darkened
  75,9,and the sun and the moon are brought together
  75,10,"on that Day man will say, “Where is the escape?”"
  75,11,No indeed! There will be no refuge
  75,12,On that Day all will end up before your Lord
  75,13,On that Day man will be informed of what he has sent forth and left behind
  75,14,"In fact, man will be a witness against himself"
  75,15,despite the excuses he may put forward
  75,16,"Do not move your tongue [O Prophet] in haste trying to memorize it"
  75,17,It is upon Us to make you memorize and recite it
  75,18,"Then when We recite it [through Gabriel], follow its recitation attentively"
  75,19,then it is upon Us to explain its meanings
  75,20,"No indeed! You [people] love this fleeting world"
  75,21,and neglect the Hereafter
  75,22,On that Day some faces will be bright
  75,23,looking at their Lord
  75,24,"And on that Day, some faces will be gloomy"
  75,25,knowing that a crushing calamity will befall them
  75,26,"Indeed, when the soul reaches the throat"
  75,27,"and it is said, “Is there any healer?”"
  75,28,And he realizes that it is time to depart
  75,29,"when legs are brought together [in a shroud]"
  75,30,"on that Day, he will be driven to your Lord"
  75,31,He neither believed nor prayed
  75,32,rather he denied and turned away
  75,33,then went swaggering to his people
  75,34,"Woe to you [O man], and woe"
  75,35,"Again, woe to you, and woe"
  75,36,Does man think that he will be left neglected
  75,37,Was he not once a drop of semen emitted
  75,38,"then he became a clinging clot, then He created him and perfected his form"
  75,39,"and made from him both genders, male and female"
  75,40,Is not He able to bring the dead back to life
  76,1,"Was there not a period of time when man was not a thing [even] mentioned"
  76,2,"Indeed, We created man from a drop of mixed fluids, in order to test him. So We gave him hearing and sight"
  76,3,"Indeed, We showed him the way, whether he is grateful or ungrateful"
  76,4,"We have surely prepared for the disbelievers chains, shackles, and a Blazing Fire"
  76,5,"Indeed, the righteous will drink from a cup [of wine] flavored with camphor"
  76,6,"a spring from which Allah’s slaves will drink, which will flow as they wish"
  76,7,They fulfill their vows and fear a Day whose evil will spread far and wide
  76,8,"and they give food, despite their love for it, to the needy, the orphans, and the captives"
  76,9,"[saying to themselves] “We feed you only for the sake of Allah; we seek from you neither reward nor gratitude"
  76,10,We fear from our Lord a grim and distressful Day.”
  76,11,"So Allah will protect them from the evil of that Day, and will grant them radiance and delight"
  76,12,and will reward them for their perseverance with Paradise and garments of silk
  76,13,They will recline therein on adorned couches; neither feeling scorching heat nor freezing cold
  76,14,"with shady branches spread above them, and clusters of fruit will be made within their reach"
  76,15,They will be served frequently with silver vessels and crystal cups
  76,16,"crystalline goblets of silver, filled precisely as desired"
  76,17,"They will be given a glass [of wine] flavored with ginger"
  76,18,from a spring therein called Salsabīl
  76,19,"They will be served by eternal young boys; if you see them, you would think that they are scattered pearls"
  76,20,"If you were to look around, you would see bliss and a vast dominion"
  76,21,"They will be dressed in garments of fine green silk and rich brocade, and will be adorned with bracelets of silver, and their Lord will give them a pure drink"
  76,22,"[And they will be told,] “Indeed, this is your reward, and your efforts have been appreciated.”"
  76,23,"Indeed, it is We Who have sent down the Qur’an to you in stages"
  76,24,"So be patient with your Lord’s decree, and do not obey any sinner or disbeliever from among them"
  76,25,And remember the Name of your Lord morning and evening
  76,26,"and prostrate to Him at night, and glorify Him at length by night"
  76,27,"Indeed, these [pagans] love this fleeting life and pay no heed to a heavy Day ahead of them"
  76,28,"It is We Who created them and strengthened their build. If We will, We can replace them with others like them"
  76,29,"Indeed, this is a reminder; so let anyone who wills may take a way to his Lord"
  76,30,"But you cannot will unless Allah wills. Indeed, Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  76,31,"He admits whom He wills into His mercy, but for the wrongdoers He has prepared a painful punishment"
  77,1,"By those [winds] sent forth in succession"
  77,2,those that blow violently
  77,3,"and scatter [rainclouds] far and wide"
  77,4,"And by those [angels] who bring criterion"
  77,5,and those who deliver revelation
  77,6,leaving no excuse or giving warning –
  77,7,what you are promised will surely come to pass
  77,8,So when the stars are extinguished
  77,9,and when the sky is split apart
  77,10,and when the mountains are blown away
  77,11,and when the messengers are summoned
  77,12,until which Day has all this been postponed
  77,13,Until the Day of Judgment
  77,14,How do you know what the Day of Judgment is
  77,15,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,16,Did We not destroy the earlier nations
  77,17,Then We will do likewise to the later ones
  77,18,This is how We deal with the wicked
  77,19,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,20,Did We not create you from a worthless fluid
  77,21,then We placed it in a secure repository
  77,22,for a determined period
  77,23,For We determined it; How excellently We determine
  77,24,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,25,Have We not made the earth a receptacle
  77,26,for the living and the dead
  77,27,"and placed therein firm towering mountains, and given you fresh water to drink"
  77,28,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,29,"[They will be told,] “Proceed to that [Fire] which you used to deny"
  77,30,"Proceed to the shadow [of smoke] ascending in three columns"
  77,31,that provides neither shade nor protection from the flames
  77,32,"Indeed, it [Hell] throws up sparks as big as castles"
  77,33,as if they were tawny camels
  77,34,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,35,On that Day they won’t speak
  77,36,nor will they be allowed to make excuses
  77,37,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,38,"[They will be told,] “This is the Day of Judgment: We have gathered you along with the earlier generations"
  77,39,"So if you have any scheme, then plot it against Me.”"
  77,40,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,41,"Indeed, the righteous will be amid shades and springs"
  77,42,and will have whatever fruit they desire
  77,43,"[They will be told,] “Eat and drink joyfully, as a reward for what you used to do.”"
  77,44,This is how We reward those who do good
  77,45,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,46,“Eat and enjoy yourselves for a while; you are truly wicked.”
  77,47,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,48,"When it is said to them, “Bow [in prayer]”, they do not bow"
  77,49,Woe on that Day to the deniers
  77,50,"In which message after this [Qur’an] will they believe"